description:
Original: 
Night 1 data. I'm mostly seeing what I have. Getting green and purple in the image that's been a pain to remove, but data looks good so far.
B:
Found a video by Visibledark Asto to fix the green and purple in the image. Worked perfectly.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TVbfsHwCAbQ
D:
Boosted color a bit. Added color dodge to give it a bit of a glow. Not sure if I like this better, but it will be replaced after I get more data anyway.
E:
After Night 2 of imaging. I over stretched the images on this one and lost a lot of data. I'll be trying a new processing method next time so haven't fixed it yet.
F:
New method from Visbledark Astro found here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j5zsZbHXrFE
I'm not sure if I'm a fan of the stars and there seems to be a lot of noise. I'll work on combining our methods for the next revision.
G:
Mix between my old method and some items from the new one. I'm not really sure what looks good anymore.
H:
I think this is going to be it for a while. More data added and reprocessed. The colors don't pop as much as previous pictures, but I kind of like it that way.
title: IC1396 - Elephant's Trunk Nebula
